Title: STEERING COLUMN: STEERING COLUMN ASSEMBLY: INSTALLATION; 2016 - 2022 MY Prius [11/2015 -        ]

INSTALLATION

PROCEDURE

1. ALIGN FRONT WHEELS FACING STRAIGHT AHEAD

2. INSTALL STEERING COLUMN ASSEMBLY

(a) Install the steering column assembly with the bolt and 2 nuts.

Torque:

36 N·m {367 kgf·cm, 27 ft·lbf}

(b) Connect each connector and engage each clamp to the steering column assembly.

(c) Engage the clamp.

(d) Connect the 2 connectors.

3. INSTALL NO. 2 STEERING INTERMEDIATE SHAFT ASSEMBLY

(a) Align the matchmarks on the No. 2 steering intermediate shaft assembly and steering column assembly.

*a

Matchmark

Install in this direction

(b) Install the No. 2 steering intermediate shaft assembly to the steering column assembly.

(c) Install the bolt.

Torque:

64 N·m {653 kgf·cm, 47 ft·lbf}

4. CONNECT NO. 2 STEERING INTERMEDIATE SHAFT ASSEMBLY

(a) Align the matchmarks on the No. 2 steering intermediate shaft assembly and steering gear assembly.

*a

Matchmark

Connect in this direction

(b) Connect the No. 2 steering intermediate shaft assembly to the steering gear assembly.

(c) Install the bolt.

Torque:

64 N·m {653 kgf·cm, 47 ft·lbf}

5. INSTALL COLUMN HOLE COVER SILENCER SHEET

(a) Engage the 2 claws to install the column hole cover silencer sheet.

(b) Engage the claw to close the column hole cover silencer sheet.

6. INSTALL STOP LIGHT SWITCH ASSEMBLY

Click here

7. INSTALL NO. 1 AIR DUCT

(a) Engage the 3 claws to install a new No. 1 air duct.

(b) Install the 2 bolts.

Torque:

9.8 N·m {100 kgf·cm, 87 in·lbf}

8. INSTALL FRONT NO. 1 CONSOLE BOX INSERT

Click here

9. INSTALL LOWER CENTER INSTRUMENT CLUSTER FINISH PANEL SUB-ASSEMBLY

Click here

10. INSTALL REAR CONSOLE BOX ASSEMBLY

Click here

11. INSTALL LOWER NO. 1 INSTRUMENT PANEL AIRBAG ASSEMBLY

Click here

12. INSTALL TURN SIGNAL SWITCH ASSEMBLY WITH SPIRAL CABLE SUB-ASSEMBLY

NOTICE:

  • Do not replace the spiral cable with sensor sub-assembly with the auxiliary battery connected and the power switch on (IG).
  • Do not rotate the spiral cable with sensor sub-assembly without the steering wheel assembly installed with the auxiliary battery connected and the power switch on (IG).
  • Ensure that the steering wheel assembly is installed and aligned straight when inspecting the steering sensor.

(a) Engage the 3 claws to install the turn signal switch assembly with spiral cable sub-assembly to the steering column assembly.

(b) Connect each connector to the turn signal switch assembly with spiral cable sub-assembly.

13. INSTALL UPPER STEERING COLUMN COVER

(a) Engage the 2 claws and 4 clips to connect the upper steering column cover.

(b) Engage the claw to install the upper steering column cover.

14. INSTALL LOWER STEERING COLUMN COVER SUB-ASSEMBLY

NOTICE:

If the lower steering column cover sub-assembly is installed in the incorrect order, the parts may break.

(a) Engage the 3 claws as shown in the illustration.

Install in this Direction

(b) Engage the 2 claws.

(c) Install the 2 screws.

Torque:

2.0 N·m {20 kgf·cm, 18 in·lbf}

15. ALIGN FRONT WHEELS FACING STRAIGHT AHEAD
